282a5f39-c335-4156-8ea9-0a796ffbd2b7.name: DISPOSITIONS_API_CALL
282a5f39-c335-4156-8ea9-0a796ffbd2b7.description: Upon conclusion of the IVR portion of the customer interaction, use this API to determine the disposition of the call, i.e., what should happen next.This resource is being done as an RPC call due to the amount of data that needs to be sent from the client when it is called
282a5f39-c335-4156-8ea9-0a796ffbd2b7.notes:
Model
Example Value
disposition {
messages (Array[message], optional): 
Array of messages to be played before the end of the call in the IVR.
,
routingEngineData (inline_model, optional)
}
message {
messageName (string): Name that indicates what message should be played
,
messageType (string): Type of message= ['PartnerDisclosure', 'ByPassDisclosure', 'StateSpecificDisclosure', 'CommercialLinesDisclosure', 'FCRA', 'Marketing', 'Priority', 'Alert', 'Transfer', 'MaintenanceWindow', 'DocumentRequest', 'PolicyStatus', 'PersonalizedMessage', 'UpfrontPaymentWarning', 'USPS', 'Other']string
Enum: "PartnerDisclosure", "ByPassDisclosure", "StateSpecificDisclosure", "CommercialLinesDisclosure", "FCRA", "Marketing", "Priority", "Alert", "Transfer", "MaintenanceWindow", "DocumentRequest", "PolicyStatus", "PersonalizedMessage", "UpfrontPaymentWarning", "USPS", "Other"
,
messageText (string, optional): Text of the content of the message to be played via Text-To-Speech if a pre-recorded file isn't found on the system.
,
forcePlay (boolean, optional): Flag indicating whether the caller should be forced to listen to the message prior to continuing.
}
inline_model {
icmDialedNumber (string): Dialed number to use when contacting the ICM.
,
callVariables (Array[callVariable], optional): Name/Value pairs for the call variables that should be sent with the routing request.
,
eccVariables (Array[eccVariable], optional):Name/Value pairs for the ECC(Expanded Call Context) variables that should be sent with the routing request.
}
callVariable {
name (string): The name of the call variable to set.
,
value (string): Value to set for the call variable.
}
eccVariable {
name (string): The name of the ECC variable to set.
,
value (string): Value to set for the ECC variable.
}

flowDiagram.text: Policies will be pulled in the order they're returned in the array.

The values played for the dynamic version will need to each be determined based on related values.  Each data point: Status, last 4 Policy Number, and State are each determined separately, and all or none can play.
- Always play product / riskType
- If any policies have the same riskType and any of the same riskType have unique policyStatus (and none are "NULL" for any policy), play the policy status.
- If any policies have the same riskType, no unique statuses for that riskType (or any "NULL" status), and unique policyState for those same risk types, then play policy state.
- If any policies have the same risk, policy status (or any "NULL") and policy State, then play last 4 policy digits.

96382005-095d-493d-b6a3-bf7d1d1b74b7.notes: Need to pull up risk type if it exists; use policy type if not.

The values played for the dynamic version will need to each be determined based on related values.  Each data point: Status, last 4 Policy Number, and State are each determined separately, and all or none can play.
- Always play product / riskType

c3bf9d6c-a72f-48a5-a3c0-ac8297d80c6e.description: Identify and authorize a policy for a policy holder.

flowDiagram.text:
This will now check against the SET_TO_FILTER_POLICIES (custom name) flag.  
This will also now have special rules for filtering with Truck and Trailer product-type intents.:
Truck: Will check against all policies returned, 
if Commercial and Auto both returned, will filter and prompt for all commercial and auto policies
If No Commercial nor Auto, will treat as no matching policies returned
If No Commercial, but Auto will only use the Auto
If Commercial, No Auto, will only use the Commercial
-
If Trailer (non Travel Trailer or Commercial Trailer):
If No Commercial nor Auto, will not set any policies, and will now point to a specific business use question
If Both Commercial and Auto, will not set any policies, and will now point to a specific business use question
If Commercial, but No Auto, will only use the Commercial
If No Commercial, but Auto, will only use the Auto.
-
If Auto (Van):
if Commercial and Auto both returned, will set to Auto
If No Commercial and no Auto, will treat as no matching policies returned
If No Commercial, but Auto will only use the Auto
If Commercial, No Auto, will only use the Commercial

Billing Tag for "Claim ID (Policy or Claim # Capture) (T27)"
This will truly count at call-end, checking against each ID and ID/Auth tag to only tag once, per policy identified, using the following priority (first has highest priority):
"Identification And Authentication by Last 4 digits of SSN, D.O.B., and Zip Code (Policy Holder) (T42)",
"Identification And Authentication by Policy Number plus Last 4 digits of SSN or D.O.B. (T4b)", 
"Identification and Authentication by ANI plus Last 4 digits of SSN or D.O.B. (T4a)", 
"Claim ID (Policy or Claim # Capture) (T27)", 
"ID ONLY by policy (T26)", "ANI_Confirm/Select Policy (T40)"

27229868-be94-42df-a18c-3737e4a745d3.name: MORE_THAN_2_POLICY_DISAMBIG_NON_PH

flowDiagram.text:
The values played for the dynamic version will need to each be determined based on related values.  Each data point: Status, last 4 Policy Number, and State are each determined separately, and all or none can play.
- Always play product / riskType
- If any policies have the same riskType and any of the same riskType have different policyStatus (and none are "NULL" for any policy), play the policy status.
- If any policies have the same riskType with different States then play the State regardless of the policy status.
- If any policies have the same risk, policy status (or any "NULL") and policy State, then play last 4 policy digits.

27229868-be94-42df-a18c-3737e4a745d3.notes: Need to pull up risk type if it exists; use policy type if not.

The values played for the dynamic version will need to each be determined based on related values.  Each data point: Status, last 4 Policy Number, and State are each determined separately, and all or none can play.
- Always play product / riskType
- If any policies have the same riskType and any of the same riskType have unique policyStatus (where none, for any policy are "NULL"), play the policy status.
- If any policies have the same riskType, no unique statuses for that riskType, and unique policyState for those same risk types, then play policy state.
- If any policies have the same risk, policy status and policy State, then play last 4 policy digits.
